.SH "NAME"
dmarc_httpd: a web server for DMARC validation and report viewing
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
A \s-1HTTP\s0 interface for:
.IP "\(bu" 4
local \s-1DMARC\s0 reports
.IP "\(bu" 4
\&\s-1DMARC\s0 validator service
.PP
Start the \s-1HTTP\s0 server:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    dmarc_httpd
.Ve
.PP
Connect with a web browser to http://localhost:8080 <http://localhost:8080/>.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
The \s-1HTTP\s0 server handles 4 types of requests:
.IP "\(bu" 4
/
.Sp
Serves files stored in the perl share directory of the Mail::DMARC module.
This presently entails one \s-1HTML\s0 file and a handful of \s-1CSS\s0 and \s-1JS\s0 files for
the report viewing feature.
.IP "\(bu" 4
/dmarc/json/validate \- \s-1DMARC\s0 validation requests
.Sp
Accepts a \s-1JSON\s0 encoded \s-1HTTP POST\s0 request. Validates the request, performs a
\&\s-1DMARC\s0 validation and returns a \s-1JSON\s0 encoded result object. This is the \s-1API\s0
for non-perl applications to utilize Mail::DMARC.
.Sp
See the dmarc_http_client app for a usage example.
.IP "\(bu" 4
/dmarc/json/report
.Sp
Accepts \s-1AJAX\s0 requests from the browser and returns \s-1JSON\s0 encoded \s-1DMARC\s0 reports.
.IP "\(bu" 4
/dmarc/json/row
.Sp
Accepts \s-1AJAX\s0 requests from the browser and returns \s-1JSON\s0 encoded \s-1DMARC\s0 report rows.
.PP
An implementation that uses the http validation service is the included <dmarc_http_client> and another is the dmarc plugin in the <Haraka mail server|http://haraka.github.io>.
.PP
A Sample Report <http://search.cpan.org/dist/Mail-DMARC/example/report_cgi.png> is available which shows the web interface. It is implemented almost entirely in JavaScript, using jQuery, jQueryUI, and jqGrid.
.PP
Web server settings are in the [http] and [https] sections of mail\-dmarc.ini.
